      <example>
        <statement>
          <p>
            Use the table below to answer the questions that follow.
          </p>
          <tabular halign="left" top="medium" left="medium" right="medium">
            <row bottom="medium" header="yes">
              <cell>Money deposit</cell>
              <cell>Percentage <m>(\%)</m> interest earned per year</cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell><m>sh\,1\,000\,-\,sh\,4\,999</m></cell>
              <cell><m>2\,\%</m></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell><m>sh\,5\,000\,-\,sh\,9\,999</m></cell>
              <cell><m>3\,\%</m></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell><m>sh\,10\,000\,-\,sh\,14\,999</m></cell>
              <cell><m>4\,\%</m></cell>
            </row>
            <row>
              <cell><m>sh\,15\,000\,-\,sh\,19\,999</m></cell>
              <cell><m>5\,\%</m></cell>
            </row>
            <row bottom="medium">
              <cell> Above <m>sh\,19\,999</m></cell>
              <cell><m>6\,\%</m></cell>
            </row>
          </tabular>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  How much interest is earned by saving the following amount 
                  of money?
                </p>
                <p>
                  <m>\text{a)} \, sh\, 4\,500 \qquad \text{b)} \, sh\, 16\,000 </m>
                </p>
                
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  What will be the total amount of money at the end of the year when one saves 
                  <m>sh\,17\,500</m>?
                </p>
              </li>
            </ol>
          </p>
        </statement>
        <solution>
          <p>
            <ol>
              <li>
                <p>
                  a) <m>sh\, 4\,500</m> is in the range <m>sh\, 1\,000\,-\,4\,999</m>. It earns an iterest of <m>2\%</m> per year.
                </p>
                <p>
                  <md>
                    <mrow>\text{Interest} =\amp 2\% \, \text{of} \, sh\, 4\,500</mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{2}{100} \times sh\, 4\,500  </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp  {\color{blue} sh\,90}</mrow>
                  </md>
                </p>
                <p>
                  b) <m>sh\, 16\,000</m> is in the range <m>sh\, 15\,000\,-\,19\,999</m>. It earns an iterest of <m>5\%</m> per year.
                </p>
                <p>
                  <md>
                    <mrow>\text{Interest} =\amp 5\% \, \text{of} \, sh\, 16\,000</mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{5}{100} \times sh\, 16\,000  </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp  {\color{blue} sh\,800}</mrow>
                  </md>
                </p>
              </li>
              <li>
                <p>
                  <md>
                    <mrow>\text{Interest} =\amp 5\% \text{of} \, sh\, 17\,500 </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp \frac{5}{100} \times sh\, 17\,500 </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp {\color{green} sh\, 875} </mrow>
                    <mrow> \text{Total amount of money} =\amp \text{Money deposited} + \text{Interest} </mrow>
                    <mrow> =\amp sh\, 17\,500+ {\color{green} sh\, 875} </mrow>
                    <mrow> = \amp {\color{blue} sh\, 18\,375} </mrow>
                  </md>
                </p>
              </li>


            </ol>
          </p>
        </solution>
      </example>
      
